                <note rend="inline" type="source">325.1121 Bethune, Larry K./15: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to the
                        Ambassador in Chile</hi> (<persName type="to">
                        <hi rend="italic">Culbertson</hi>
                    </persName>)</head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1931-03-28T12:00:00-05:00"
                            >March 28, 1931—noon</date>.</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>16. The General Motors Export Company had advised the Department of the receipt
                    of information indicating that a number of the <pb facs="1049" n="935"
                        xml:id="pg_935"/> General Motors’ representatives in Chile have received
                    threats of personal violence, and that in view of the actual assault on Mr. V.
                    M. Kaminsky, who had likewise been so threatened, it is desired that the Embassy
                    undertake to have adequate protection extended to them.</p>
                <p>If in your opinion such action is necessary you may informally and in a most
                    friendly manner bring the apprehensions of this important American company
                    regarding the safety of its personnel to the attention of the appropriate
                    authorities.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Stimson</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
